parameters: \n<Manu><WordWrap>Excuse me, but are you Paz Latchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>In the flesh. So who are you and what do you want from me?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>My name is Manu and I came here to compete in the contest and...
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Contest? You wanted to join the contest and yet your here? Isn't it a bit odd?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>If you wanted to join the contest you should have joined earlier.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Well that's the thing, I wasn't able to reach the contest because...

\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>So you came here for a second cahnce on entering the contest am I right? Forget it. If you wanted to achieve your goals you should have focused that in front of you not the mishaps beside you.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Sorry but I am not giving you a second chance, its not worth my time.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Just so you know, your servant Belle she said to me that you might give me a chance since I helped your restairant.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>HOLD ON! What do you mean by helping my restaurant?

\n<Manu><WordWrap>Thats right, I followed the scent of your delicious batchoy that led me into your restaurant. And when you were under staffed and Belle was trying to figure out what to do, I heped serving the people your batchoy around.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Belle told me that you could give me another shot at the contest since I did a favor to you somewhat, but that seems impossible now.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>So you helped around my restaurant, and served the customers as well?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You know what I'll give you a second chance, but not a traditional contest. More like a mock contest so to speak.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Ofcourse I am serious. If you can provve to me that you can cook or better prove that you want to be a chef then I'll allow you to proceed to the next challenge.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Since this is not a traditional contest, I will have a personal contest with you.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>The challenge is simple. I want you to gather information on the recipe for batchoy, in order to create my famous batchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>But there's a catch you can only get the information from the people inside this market and you have to guess what ingredients is right.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You can ask for people what the ingredients are but make sure to pick the right ones. Also come back to me as soon as you "know" the recipe itself.

\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You have 7 minutes to collect all ingredients and present it to me. I will ask some questions that relates to the ingredients of the dish. If you fail answering I will have no choice but to let you fail, but if you win I'll give you a chance. So do we got a deal?
Head to the Jaro Market place and interact with the people to get information

Find the ingredients of Paz's batchoy
before the timer runs out and guess each ingredient correctly.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Go around the market and ask people for the ingredioents for batchoy and come back to me once you got all the ingredients.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>So have you asked the people in the market about the batchoy's recipe?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>I was able to ask the people in the market and got all the information about the recipe for batchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Good, then I'll be questioning you whether or not you have payed attention on the people's answers.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>If you failed answering the question I have no choice but decline your chance of competing in the competition.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>I'll be asking 5 questions. Get 3 questions wrong I'll have no choice but to end your journey here.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>First question. What is the base for batchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Second question. What is the meat of choice in batchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Third question. What is the long stand of pasta called that is paired with batchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Fourth question. What seasoning do you use when making batchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Last question. What toppings do you put in a batchoy?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You passed! But that doesn't mean you have completed the challenge yet.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>For this final challenge I want you to make batchoy itself.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>I'll give you the recipe, however you need to make the broth of the batchoy itself. For it is the heart of the dish.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You see that sove over there, the bown looking object, I want you to cook the broth right there.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>In cooking its not just recognizing the dish but mastering the craft itself.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>If you can create the broth itself, then we can proceed in creating the batchoy itself.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>I will be giving you a few minutes to complete the broth itself. Time is of importance when cooking, you cannot expect that people will like your food if its cold no?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You have 10 minutes to finish cooking the broth.
Head towards the stove to make Batchoy broth
Quest Updated. Press "ESC" to view the quest in the menu tab.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Complete creating the batchoy's broth before the timer runs out.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Come back to me once you finished creating the broth so we can make this batchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You don't have a lot of time. NOW HURRY

Head towards the stove to make Batchoy broth
Press "ENTER" to interact with the stove
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>It seems you were able to create the batchoy broth, Good. Here have the batchoy recipe.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Here are some noodles for you to create the batchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Now I want you to craft the batchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Give it to me once you crafted the batchoy.
Open your menu by pressing "ESC" to craft Batchoy and give it to Paz latchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Very good. Now you understand the meanign of cooking?
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Cooking isn't about combining random ingredients into one. A chef must know what the right ingredients to use in cooking and to pay attention while at it.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>You need to be efficient in cooking as well, even short in time you need to be adaptive to any dish that is thrown to you.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>An an apology as well. I'm sorry for being harsh on you, I did not know that you helped around the restaurant.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>As a token of gratitude I here by grant you the opportunity to proceed to the next challenge!
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>However, since you did not participate "legally" you need a letter to the mayor of this town.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Here a letter of validation. But I do not know if the mayor would allow it.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>i hear the Mayor was at the Town hall. That all I know for now.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Don't say anything, just focus on your journey. Maybe come here to eat batchoy one in a while.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Talk to me once you have crafted the batchoy.
Open your menu by pressing "ESC" to craft Batchoy and give it to Paz latchoy.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Follow your heart towards your journey.
\n<Paz Latchoy><WordWrap>Come by here and relax once a bit.
